{
  "texts": [
    "Many risk factors are shared between pulmonary fibrosis and lung cancer and CT imaging has played a crucial role in the early detection of both diseases [8,9] Deep learning (DL) algorithms, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNNs), have been used in lung nodule detection, segmentation, and classification tasks with high accuracy and efficiency [10][11][12][13][14][15][16][17].",
    "An explainable model can be achieved with visualization maps attached to the model, specific features and structures can be highlighted in the images.",
    "This could help researchers to better understand how a model reaches decisions, and identify features associated with it [18,19].",
    "Zhu et al. [11] retain the segmented nodules by discarding the background information when performing nodule classification, and Xiao et al.",
    "[12] isolate nodules from the encompassing tissues based on the presupposition that the presence of surrounding tissue might negatively impact the classification outcome."
  ]
}